					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You might be able to take a cue from popular block stacking games: <a href="http://harddrop.com/wiki/index.php?title=Random_Generator" class="postlink">Bag randomizer</a> | <a href="http://harddrop.com/wiki/index.php?title=TGM_randomizer" class="postlink">History based randomizer</a>
<br />
<br />Tetris DS randomizes the pieces with a bag randomizer: generate 7 at a time, then reshuffle once you hit the end of the queue. LJ65 won't ever generate one of the last 3 pieces as the next pieces because it moves the generated piece to the end of the queue and picks only one of the frontmost four.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

